'''''Al-Maydӑn''''' is an [[Egypt]]ian independent weekly [[newspaper]] published in [[Arabic]].<ref>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/programmes/correspondent/1619902.stm BBC News], 26 October, 2001.</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.arabwestreport.info|title=Arab West Report {{!}} Media Research and Commentary from Egypt and the Middle East|website=www.arabwestreport.info|language=en|access-date=2018-07-18}}</ref> The paper was first published on 16 March 1995.<ref name=mezz>{{cite book|author=Mohamed Ezz Elvarab|title=Arab Memo to the Next American President|url=http://mercury.ethz.ch/serviceengine/Files/ISN/94027/ichaptersection_singledocument/e939a28e-1cff-4e13-9fe3-6cecd3276f95/en/Chapter+10.pdf|accessdate=26 September 2015|chapter=Greasing the presses|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150927160453/http://mercury.ethz.ch/serviceengine/Files/ISN/94027/ichaptersection_singledocument/e939a28e-1cff-4e13-9fe3-6cecd3276f95/en/Chapter+10.pdf|archive-date=2015-09-27|dead-url=yes|df=}}</ref> It is part of Al Maydān Inc.<ref name=mezz/> In 2001, its editor-in-chief, Mohammed Mohammed Al Mursy, was arrested and jailed for taking [[bribes]] from a producer to stop the defamation campaign against him published in the paper.<ref>{{cite news|title=Newspaper Editor Bribed to Stop Calling Egyptian Producer a ‘Car Dealer’ |url=http://www.albawaba.com/news/newspaper-editor-bribed-stop-calling-egyptian-producer-%E2%80%98car-dealer%E2%80%99 |accessdate=26 September 2015 |work=Albawaba News |date=1 July 2001 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150926135954/http://www.albawaba.com/news/newspaper-editor-bribed-stop-calling-egyptian-producer-%E2%80%98car-dealer%E2%80%99 |archivedate=September 26, 2015 }}</ref>

