{{Infobox games | name = FIS Nordic World Ski Championships 1962 | logo = | size = | caption = | host city = [[Zakopane]] | country = Poland | motto = | nations participating = | teams participating = | debuting countries = | athletes participating = | events = 10 | opening ceremony = {{Start date|1962|2|18|df=y}} | closing ceremony = {{End date|1962|2|25|df=y}} | officially opened by = | athlete's oath = | judge's oath = | torch lighter = | stadium = | length = | indprize = | tmprize = | website = | previous = [[FIS Nordic World Ski Championships 1958|1958]] | next = [[FIS Nordic World Ski Championships 1966|1966]] }} The '''FIS Nordic World Ski Championships 1962''' took place February 18–25, 1962 in [[Zakopane]], [[Poland]]. Zakopane became the second city to host the world championships three times (1929, 1939), joining [[Lahti]], [[Finland]] (1926, 1938, and 1958). Women's 5&nbsp;km and the ski jumping individual normal hill made their event debuts at these championships.
