. Aubrey Smith]], English-American cricketer and actor (d. 1948) *[[1866]] &ndash; [[Carlos Schwabe]], Swiss Symbolist painter and printmaker (d. 1926) *[[1870]] &ndash; [[Emil Orlík]], Czech painter, etcher, and lithographer (d. 1932) *[[1875]] &ndash; [[Charles Gondouin]], French rugby player and [[tug of war]] competitor (d. 1947) *[[1880]] &ndash; [[Milan Rastislav Štefánik]], Slovak astronomer, general, and politician (d. 1919) *[[1882]] &ndash; [[David Burliuk]], Ukrainian author and illustrator (d. 1967) *[[1885]] &ndash; [[Jacques Feyder]], Belgian actor, director, and screenwriter (d. 1948) *[[1891]] &ndash; [[Julius Saaristo]], Finnish javelin thrower and soldier (d. 1969) *[[1893]] &ndash; [[Hans Fallada]], German author (d. 1947) *[[1896]] &ndash; [[Sophie Bledsoe Aberle]], Native American anthropologist, physician and nutritionist (d. 1996) *[[1898]] &ndash; [[Sara Carter]], American singer-songwriter (d. 1979) *[[1899]] &ndash; [[Hart Crane]], American poet (d. 1932) * 1899 &ndash; [[Ernest Hemingway]], American novelist, short story writer, and journalist, [[Nobel Prize in Literature|Nobel Prize]] laureate (d. 1961) *[[1900]] &ndash; [[Isadora Bennett]], American theatre manager and modern dance publicity agent (d. 1980) *[[1903]] &ndash; [[Russell Lee (photographer)|Russell Lee]], American photographer and journalist (d. 1986) * 1903 &ndash; [[Roy Neuberger]], American businessman and financier, co-founded [[Neuberger Berman]] (d. 2010) *[[1908]] &ndash; [[Jug McSpaden]], American golfer and architect (d. 1996) *[[1911]] &ndash; [[Marshall McLuhan]], Canadian author and theorist (d. 1980) *[[1911]] &ndash; [[Umashankar Joshi]], Indian author, poet, and scholar (d. 1988) *[[1914]] &ndash; [[Aleksander Kreek]], Estonian shot putter and discus thrower (d. 1977) *[[1917]] &ndash; [[Alan B. Gold]], Canadian lawyer and jurist (d. 2005) *[[1920]] &ndash; [[Constant Nieuwenhuys]], Dutch painter, sculptor, and illustrator (d. 2005) * 1920 &ndash; [[Isaac Stern]], Polish violinist and conductor (d. 2001) * 1920 &ndash; [[Jean Daniel]], Algerian-French-Jewish journalist and author *[[1921]] &ndash; [[James Cooke Brown]], American sociologist and author (d. 2000) * 1921 &ndash; [[John Horsley (actor)|John Horsley]], English actor (d. 2014) * 1921 &ndash; [[Vusamazulu Credo Mutwa]], Zulu sangoma *[[1922]] &ndash; [[Kay Starr]], American singer (d. 2016) * 1922 &ndash; [[Mollie Sugden]], English actress (d. 2009) *[[1923]] &ndash; [[Rudolph A. Marcus]], Canadian-American chemist and academic, [[Nobel Prize in Chemistry|Nobel Prize]] laureate * 1923 &ndash; [[Queenie Watts]], English actress and singer (d. 1980) *[[1924]] &ndash; [[Rahimuddin Khan]], Pakistani general and politician, 7th [[Governor of Balochistan]] * 1924 &ndash; [[Don Knotts]], American actor and screenwriter (d. 2006) *[[1926]] &ndash; [[Paul Burke (actor)|Paul Burke]], American actor (d. 2009) *[[1925]] &ndash; [[Johnny Peirson]], Canadian hockey player * 1926 &ndash; [[Norman Jewison]], Canadian actor, director, and producer * 1926 &ndash; [[Bill Pertwee]], English actor (d. 2013) * 1926 &ndash; [[Karel Reisz]], Czech-English director and producer (d. 2002) *[[1928]] &ndash; [[Sky Low Low]], Canadian wrestler (d. 1998) *[[1929]] &ndash; [[Bob Orton]], American wrestler (d. 2006) *[[1930]] &ndash; [[Anand Bakshi]], Indian poet and songwriter (d. 2002) * 1930 &ndash; [[Helen Merrill]], American singer *[[1931]] &ndash; [[Sonny Clark]], American pianist and composer (d. 1963) * 1931 &ndash; [[Plas Johnson]], American saxophonist * 1931 &ndash; [[Leon Schidlowsky]], Chilean-Israeli painter and composer *[[1932]] &ndash; [[Kaye Stevens]], American singer and actress (d. 2011) *[[1933]] &ndash; [[John Gardner (American writer)|John Gardner]], American novelist, essayist, and critic (d. 1982) *[[1934]] &ndash; [[Chandu Borde]], Indian cricketer and manager * 1934 &ndash; [[Jonathan Miller]], English actor, director, and author *[[1935]] &ndash; [[Norbert Blüm]],